Data.#text: whoami - displays logged on user information

"powershell.exe" & {$credFile = \""$env:LOCALAPPDATA\file\$env:USERNAME.txt\"", if (Test-Path $credFile) {,     $cred = New-Object -TypeName System.Management.Automation.PSCredential -ArgumentList $env:USERNAME, (Get-Content $credFile | ConvertTo-SecureString),     if($cred.GetNetworkCredential().Password -eq \""onlyUPandLowChars\""){,       Write-Host -ForegroundColor Yellow \""The new password is the same as the password stored in the credential file. Please specify a different new password.\""; exit -1,     },     try {,         $newPassword = ConvertTo-SecureString onlyUPandLowChars -AsPlainText -Force,         Set-ADAccountPassword -Identity $env:USERNAME -OldPassword $cred.password -NewPassword $newPassword,     },     catch { ,         $_.Exception,         $errCode = $_.Exception.ErrorCode,         Write-Host \""Error code: $errCode\"",         if ($errCode -eq 86) {,             Write-Host -ForegroundColor Yellow \""The stored password for the current user is incorrect. Please run the prereq commands to set the correct credentials\"",             Remove-Item $credFile,         },         exit $errCode,     },     Write-Host -ForegroundColor Cyan \""Successfully changed the password to onlyUPandLowChars\"",     $newCred = New-Object System.Management.Automation.PSCredential ($env:USERNAME, $(ConvertTo-SecureString \""onlyUPandLowChars\"" -AsPlainText -Force)),     $newCred.Password | ConvertFrom-SecureString | Out-File $credFile, }, else {,     Write-Host -ForegroundColor Yellow \""You must store the password of the current user by running the prerequisite commands first\"", }}
